The paper deals with the matroid secretary problem, which is a well-studied problem in the field of online algorithms and optimization. The paper specifically focuses on the submodular matroid secretary problem and presents black-box reductions from SMSP to MSP. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the applications of the problem in mechanism design, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents improved algorithms for SMSP, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
